    ],
    "summary": "On 19 February 2014 at approximately 2140 hours, a Contract Employee was injured while tightening flanges on a closed cooler water deck during construction operations. The CE pulled a wrench to tighten a bolt, causing the wrench to slip. The CE stumbled backwards and his left foot struck an uneven space on the grating, causing the ankle to roll sideways. The CE sustained fractures to the tibia and fibula in the left ankle.",
